Projects

Project (1)
Morphological and molecular diversity of Cumacea (Crustacea; Peracarida) within Northern European Ocean ecoregions
Project
This study aims to give a first insight into the underestimated morphological and genetic variability of the peracarid order Cumacea in Icelandic and adjacent waters. Within a biogeographic survey cumaceans are used as model organisms for the investigation of the possible linkage between hydro-geographically parameter and evolutionary processes.
View
